biboAdmSnmpVersion.name: biboAdmSnmpVersion
biboAdmSnmpVersion.description: SNMP Version. version1 : SNMP version V1 version1_compat : SNMP version V1 compatibility mode without the appending private OID part (.i). This is for some SNMP managers that cannot handle this extension. In this mode rows with identical index variable content cannot be read correctly. p1 (patch1) : getnext returns the lexicographical next OID (ever!) version1p1_auto : use version1p1_compat if possible use version1p1 if nessesary Usually the OIDs have the format: .1.3.6.x.x .y.y .i .1.3.6.x.x: is the constant part of the OID of the variable specified in MIB-source .y.y : is the specific part of the OID to identify exactly a row. It is the content of all index variables. .i : is a consecutively incremented index number, to distinguish rows with identical index variables

biboAdmIpAddr.name: biboAdmIpAddr
biboAdmIpAddr.description: Local IP address. If this object is set, it's value will be used as the source address for all IP packets that are sent. Otherwise, the IP address used will be retrieved from the ipRouteTable, for the interface the IP packet is to be transmitted over.

biboAdmTrapHostTable.name: biboAdmTrapHostTable
biboAdmTrapHostTable.description: The biboAdmTrapHostTable defines where traps are sent (i.e., which hosts). If the table is empty traps are broadcasted. Creating entries: Entries are added by assigning an IP address value to the biboAdmTrapHostAddr field. Deleting entries: Entries can be removed by assigning ing the respective biboAdmTrapHostStatus field to 'delete'.

biboAdmTrapHostStatus.name: biboAdmTrapHostStatus
biboAdmTrapHostStatus.description: Status is always valid, and set to delete only to discard the whole entry.

biboAdmSyslogMaxEntries.name: biboAdmSyslogMaxEntries
biboAdmSyslogMaxEntries.description: Maximum Number of syslog messages stored in memory.

biboAdmSyslogTable.name: biboAdmSyslogTable
biboAdmSyslogTable.description: The biboAdmSyslogTable keeps track of syslog messages received. The size of the table (number of entries), is limited by the value of biboAdmSyslogMaxEntries. The columns specify attributes for each message generated. As this information only reports events on the system, all fields are read-only. Creating entries: Entries can only be created by the system and are made each time a syslog message is generated. Deleting entries: Entries are removed by the system once the size limit (biboAdmSyslogMaxEntries) is reached.

biboAdmSyslogMessage.name: biboAdmSyslogMessage
biboAdmSyslogMessage.description: The text of the syslog message.

biboAdmLogHostTable.name: biboAdmLogHostTable
biboAdmLogHostTable.description: The biboAdmLogHostTable lists hosts which are to receive syslog messages. This table also defines which types and levels of messages to send. Creating entries: Entries are created by setting a IP address to biboAdmLogHostAddr. Deleting entries: Entries are removed by setting the appropriate biboAdmLogHostLevel field to 'delete'.

biboAdmLogHostAddr.name: biboAdmLogHostAddr
biboAdmLogHostAddr.description: Ip-Address where syslog messages are sent. If the facility is set to memory or console, this field is not used.

biboAdmLogHostLevel.name: biboAdmLogHostLevel
biboAdmLogHostLevel.description: Priorities lower or equal this level are sent to loghost. The delete priority is used to discard the whole entry.

biboAdmLogHostFacility.name: biboAdmLogHostFacility
biboAdmLogHostFacility.description: The facility used for the syslog messages being generated.

biboAdmLogHostType.name: biboAdmLogHostType
biboAdmLogHostType.description: The subject of the messages that are to be generated. system means all subjects except accounting, all means all subjects.

biboAdmLogHostTimestamp.name: biboAdmLogHostTimestamp
biboAdmLogHostTimestamp.description: This object describes the format of the timestamp. none(1) = no timestamp, time(2) = only time is printed, all(3) = date and time is printed.

biboAdmConfigTable.name: biboAdmConfigTable
biboAdmConfigTable.description: The biboAdmConfigTable is used for assigning parameters for managing configuration files. Creating entries: Entries are added to this table by assigning a value to the biboAdmConfigCmd object. (i.e., The intermediate result of executing, cmd=save, creates an entry to this table.). Deleting entries: Entries can only be removed by the system and is done only after the requested action has been performed (i.e. Once the cmd=save action is complete.).

biboAdmConfigDirTable.name: biboAdmConfigDirTable
biboAdmConfigDirTable.description: Configuration directory table. This table contains all available configuration files in flash memory.

biboAdmConfigCmd.name: biboAdmConfigCmd
biboAdmConfigCmd.description: Command for configuration handling. Possible values are : save(1) = save configuration (to FLASH) load(2) = load configuration (from FLASH) put(3) = write configuration (via TFTP) get(4) = read configuration (via TFTP) state(5) = write complete configuration (via TFTP) delete(6) = delete configuration (within FLASH) move(7) = move configuration (within FLASH) copy(8) = copy configuration (within FLASH) reboot(9) = reboot the system reorg(10) = reorganizes the flash

biboAdmConfigObject.name: biboAdmConfigObject
biboAdmConfigObject.description: Table object id (OID) to save/load. If this field is set, only this table is saved/loaded. Otherwise all tables are saved/loaded.

biboAdmConfigPath.name: biboAdmConfigPath
biboAdmConfigPath.description: NAme of the configuration file in flash memory to save/load.

biboAdmConfigPathNew.name: biboAdmConfigPathNew
biboAdmConfigPathNew.description: New name of configuration file in flash memory to move/copy

biboAdmConfigHost.name: biboAdmConfigHost
biboAdmConfigHost.description: TFTP host's IP address to send/receive the file to/from. The configuration is transfered directly from flash memory (biboAdmConfigPath) to TFTP-file (biboAdmConfigFile).

biboAdmConfigState.name: biboAdmConfigState
biboAdmConfigState.description: The state of this command (i.e., biboAdmConfigCmd). todo(1) = The command has not started; running(2) = The command is executing; done(3) = The command successfully completed; error(4) = The command failed (see the biboAdmSyslogTable).

biboAdmConfigFile.name: biboAdmConfigFile
biboAdmConfigFile.description: TFTP filename to read/write from/to the specified host. The configuration file received is stored in flash memory specified by biboAdmConfigPath. The actual configuration is not changed.

biboAdmConfigDirName.name: biboAdmConfigDirName
biboAdmConfigDirName.description: Name of the configuration file in flash memory.

biboAdmConfigDirCount.name: biboAdmConfigDirCount
biboAdmConfigDirCount.description: Number of tables saved in the file.

biboAdmConfigDirContent.name: biboAdmConfigDirContent
biboAdmConfigDirContent.description: Description of directory's contents (e.g., <all> or a series of table numbers).

biboAdmBoardTable.name: biboAdmBoardTable
biboAdmBoardTable.description: The biboAdmBoardTable lists information about the installed communications modules. This table is updated after every system boot up. Creating entries: Entries are created by the system upon detecting the installed hardware. Deleting entries: Entries are removed by the system as a result of removed hardware.

biboABrdSlot.name: biboABrdSlot
biboABrdSlot.description: The slot, or location of this module.

biboABrdHWRelease.name: biboABrdHWRelease
biboABrdHWRelease.description: The hardware release of this module.

biboABrdFWRelease.name: biboABrdFWRelease
biboABrdFWRelease.description: The firmware release of this module.

biboABrdPartNo.name: biboABrdPartNo
biboABrdPartNo.description: The part number of this module.

biboABrdConnector.name: biboABrdConnector
biboABrdConnector.description: The type of connector used for this module. For modules with more than one connector this value can be changed/switched by setting this object. For example, the CM-BNCTP module supports both twisted pair (RJ45) and 10Base2 (BNC) connectors. If this object is set to 'AUTO' then the BRICK will automatically detect which connector type is being used.

biboABrdUnit.name: biboABrdUnit
biboABrdUnit.description: The logical unit number of this interface.

biboABrdSerialNo.name: biboABrdSerialNo
biboABrdSerialNo.description: The serial number of this module.

biboAdmUsrTrapTable.name: biboAdmUsrTrapTable
biboAdmUsrTrapTable.description: The biboAdmUsrTrapTable lists user-defined objects that are used to create traps. These traps are sent locally, but can also be sent to remote hosts using the biboAdmTrapHostTable. Creating entries: Entries are created by assigning the biboATrpObj object a valid object identifier. Deleting entries: Entries are removed by setting the entry's biboATrpStatus object to 'delete'.

biboATrpObj.name: biboATrpObj
biboATrpObj.description: The object identifier of an object to use. Each time this object's value changes, a trap is created and sent. Either a single leaf (single variable) or a table (of objects) can be specified.

biboATrpStatus.name: biboATrpStatus
biboATrpStatus.description: The status of this entry. Upon creation of a new entry, this object's value is set to 'valid'.

biboAdmNameServ2.name: biboAdmNameServ2
biboAdmNameServ2.description: IP address of second name server.

biboAdmBridgeEnable.name: biboAdmBridgeEnable
biboAdmBridgeEnable.description: Sets bridging to enable / disable status.

biboAdmCapiTcpPort.name: biboAdmCapiTcpPort
biboAdmCapiTcpPort.description: TCP port for remote CAPI demon.

biboAdmRipUdpPort.name: biboAdmRipUdpPort
biboAdmRipUdpPort.description: UDP port for RIP. Setting this object to zero disables RIP.

biboAdmSWVersion.name: biboAdmSWVersion
biboAdmSWVersion.description: This is the software release version

biboAdmTimeServer.name: biboAdmTimeServer
biboAdmTimeServer.description: The IP address of the time server.

biboAdmTimeOffset.name: biboAdmTimeOffset
biboAdmTimeOffset.description: This is the time offset from GMT in seconds. If the set value is in the range from -24 to 24, it means hours, and is automatically converted to seconds.

biboAdmConsoleSyslog.name: biboAdmConsoleSyslog
biboAdmConsoleSyslog.description: Specifies whether to direct syslog messages to the console.

biboAdmSyslogTableLevel.name: biboAdmSyslogTableLevel
biboAdmSyslogTableLevel.description: Specifies which message levels to post to the biboAdmSyslogTable and the console, if applicable.

biboAdmSystemId.name: biboAdmSystemId
biboAdmSystemId.description: This object contains the system Identification String.

biboAdmLicInfoTable.name: biboAdmLicInfoTable
biboAdmLicInfoTable.description: This table contains an entry for each feature, that can be activated by a license. The licenses have to be entered in the biboAdmLicenseTable. This tabl indicates the current state of the different licenses.

biboAdmLicInfoStatus.name: biboAdmLicInfoStatus
biboAdmLicInfoStatus.description: The current state of the license.

biboAdmLicInfoId.name: biboAdmLicInfoId
biboAdmLicInfoId.description: The complete serial id string of the special license.

biboAdmLicInfoSlot.name: biboAdmLicInfoSlot
biboAdmLicInfoSlot.description: In case of a hardware license corresponding to a dedicated module serial number, it is the slot number of the module.

biboAdmLicInfoMaxLic.name: biboAdmLicInfoMaxLic
biboAdmLicInfoMaxLic.description: The max number of allowed chunks.

biboAdmLicInfoInUse.name: biboAdmLicInfoInUse
biboAdmLicInfoInUse.description: The current number of chunks in use.

biboAdmLicInfoHwSerial.name: biboAdmLicInfoHwSerial
biboAdmLicInfoHwSerial.description: The complete serial id string of the special license.

biboAdmLicInfoUnit.name: biboAdmLicInfoUnit
biboAdmLicInfoUnit.description: In case of a hardware license corresponding to a dedicated module serial number, it is the unit number of the module.

biboAdmBootpRelayServer.name: biboAdmBootpRelayServer
biboAdmBootpRelayServer.description: This object contains the destination IP address to which BOOTP/DHCP request are forwarded by the BIANCA/BRICK BOOTP relay agent. If this entry is empty no BOOTP forwarding is done.

biboAdmRadiusServer.name: biboAdmRadiusServer
biboAdmRadiusServer.description: This object contains the IP address of the RADIUS server (remote dial in user service). If set to 0.0.0.0 RADIUS services are generally disabled (default). The corresponding Radius password is configured in the biboAdmRadiusSecret variable.

biboAdmLocalPPPIdent.name: biboAdmLocalPPPIdent
biboAdmLocalPPPIdent.description: This is the local ID string used for PPP authentication (PAP/CHAP). In pre4.3 versions the sysName has been used as the local ID string. This is, for increased ease and transparency of system configuration, no longer true.

biboAdmHttpTcpPort.name: biboAdmHttpTcpPort
biboAdmHttpTcpPort.description: TCP port for the HTTP server. Default port is 80, 0 disables the HTTP server.

biboAdmTapiTcpPort.name: biboAdmTapiTcpPort
biboAdmTapiTcpPort.description: TCP port for remote TAPI demon.

biboAdmTimeProtocol.name: biboAdmTimeProtocol
biboAdmTimeProtocol.description: This field specifies from which source the bricks internal clock is synchronised: none(1) = no time synchronisation time-udp(2) = UDP/TIME (RFC 868), from biboAdmTimeServer time-tcp(3) = TCP/TIME (RFC 868), from biboAdmTimeServer time-sntp(4) = SNTP (RFC 1769), from biboAdmTimeServer isdn(5) = examines ISDN time, from controller stack 0

biboAdmTimeUpdate.name: biboAdmTimeUpdate
biboAdmTimeUpdate.description: This is the intervall for timeserver requests (in seconds). If the set value is in the range from -24 to 24, it means hours, and is automatically converted to seconds. If the time comes from ISDN, the time is updated with the next call after this intervall.

biboAdmWINS1.name: biboAdmWINS1
biboAdmWINS1.description: The IP address of the WINS server (NetBIOS Name Server).

biboAdmWINS2.name: biboAdmWINS2
biboAdmWINS2.description: The IP address of the alternate WINS server.

biboACrdSlot.name: biboACrdSlot
biboACrdSlot.description: The slot, or location of this card.

biboACrdTemp.name: biboACrdTemp
biboACrdTemp.description: This variable shows the actual card temperature in the unit Celsius.

biboACrdTempAlarmTrap.name: biboACrdTempAlarmTrap
biboACrdTempAlarmTrap.description: If the card temperature raises above the threshold, a trap is generated every 60 seconds.

biboAdmTrapACrdTempCritical.name: biboAdmTrapACrdTempCritical
biboAdmTrapACrdTempCritical.description: This trap signifies that the Card temperature raises above the critical alarm-threshold

biboAdmTrapACrdTempOk.name: biboAdmTrapACrdTempOk
biboAdmTrapACrdTempOk.description: A normal Card temperature has been restored.

biboAdmTrapACrdDown.name: biboAdmTrapACrdDown
biboAdmTrapACrdDown.description: This trap signifies that the specified Card is down

biboAdmTrapACrdRunning.name: biboAdmTrapACrdRunning
biboAdmTrapACrdRunning.description: This trap signifies that the specified Card is up/running

biboAdmTrapACrdFailed.name: biboAdmTrapACrdFailed
biboAdmTrapACrdFailed.description: This trap signifies that the specified Card has failed

biboAdmTrapACrdStopped.name: biboAdmTrapACrdStopped
biboAdmTrapACrdStopped.description: This trap signifies that the specified Card is stopped

biboAdmSnmpLinkTrapEvent.name: biboAdmSnmpLinkTrapEvent
biboAdmSnmpLinkTrapEvent.description: Defines the ifOperStatus transition(s) of an ifTable object that generates a SNMP linkUp/linkDown trap: none : disable linkUp/linkDown trap generation. any : enable bintec like trap generation. - entering the up state generates a up trap - any other state change generates a down trap up : enable rfc1157 like trap generation. - entering the up state generates a up trap - leaving the up state generates a down trap down : enable rfc2233 like trap generation. - leaving the down state generates a up trap - entering the down state generates a down trap Seven parameters are sent in each linkUp/linkDown trap pdu: 1. ifEntry.ifIndex (mandatory for linkUp/Down traps) 2. ifEntry.ifDescr 3. ifEntry.ifType 4. ifEntry.ifAdminStatus 5. ifEntry.ifOperStatus 6. system.Description 7. system.Name

biboExtAdmMonAddress.name: biboExtAdmMonAddress
biboExtAdmMonAddress.description: The IP address of the host machine running the Activity Monitor program. This program displays the information about the current state of all interfaces. Periodically UDP packets are send to this IP address, to refresh the data automatically on the target host. The value 255.255.255.255 represents the broadcast address of the first LAN interface (e.g. 10.255.255.255), so more than one Activity Monitor on different hosts can receive the data.

biboExtAdmMonPort.name: biboExtAdmMonPort
biboExtAdmMonPort.description: UDP port for the Activity Monitor protocol.

biboExtAdmMonType.name: biboExtAdmMonType
biboExtAdmMonType.description: This parameter configures the content of the Activity Monitor packets, or disables it: off : Activity Monitor disabled physical : send only physical interfaces information physical-virt: send physical and virtual interface information.

biboExtAdmMonUpdate.name: biboExtAdmMonUpdate
biboExtAdmMonUpdate.description: This is the time interval for the Activity Monitor for sending packets (in seconds) to the specified IP address. The value of 0 disables sending Activity Monitor packets.
